ODD OR EVEN USING PROCEDURE

AIM:
Write a PL/SQL program to find a number is odd or even using procedure.

ALGORITHM:
Step1: Start
Step2: Accept a numeric input num from the user
Step3: Call the procedure odd_or_even(num)
Step4: Inside the procedure:
4.1: If the number mod 2 equals 0 then
Display "Even"
4.2: Else
Display "Odd"
Step5: Stop


CODE

CREATE OR REPLACE PROCEDURE ODD_OR_EVEN(NUM INTEGER)IS
BEGIN
IF MOD(NUM,2)=0 THEN
DBMS_OUTPUT.PUT_LINE('EVEN NUMBER');
ELSE
DBMS_OUTPUT.PUT_LINE('ODD NUMBER');
END IF;
END;
/
EXEC ODD_OR_EVEN(&num);
